data structures cell2struct >>

cell

Create cell array of empty matrices.

Syntax

C = cell()
C = cell(m)
C = cell(m, n)
C = cell(m, n, ... , p)
C = cell(sz)

Input argument

m, n, ... , p

dimensions of the cell to create.

sz

a vector of integer values (dimensions of the cell to create).

Output argument

C

a cell

Description

cell returns a cell array of empty matrices.

cell() is equivalent to cell(0)

Example

A = eye(2, 4);
sz = size(A)
C = cell(sz)

See also

struct, iscell.
